From a3367cfc2e04550e1ef08d501d2578b1ea6b6337 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 06:28:17 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix(mockdata): correct pricing math, type labels, and schema
 (Phase 1)

Data fixes:
- ucidsComputeStorage.ts: fix u1 HPE/Dell and u2 Dell totalPrice/
  originalPrice/savings to equal sum(items.unitPrice * quantity).
  Previous totals were understated by $27.9K-$181.9K against their
  own line items.
- ucidsComputeStorage.ts: resolve bi-9 (400-BPSB) unitPrice duplicate
  ($1,195 -> canonical $1,190), which was accidentally adjacent to
  the deliberate $1,590-vs-$1,190 forensic pricing-mismatch fixture.
- catalogPart2.ts: standardize 3 mislabeled standalone switches/
  gateway (sku-13, sku-15, sku-17) from 'Network Adapter' to
  'Chassis', matching the self-referencing chassisRef pattern already
  used by the two correctly-typed switches (sku-16, aruba-10000).
- catalogPart1.ts: fix NVIDIA H100 GPU mislabeled as 'Processor' ->
  new 'GPU' category.
- catalogPart1.ts/catalogPart2.ts: seed complianceFlags on one SKU
  per vendor (HPE/Dell/Cisco/Juniper) so the CLIC-warning UI path has
  real test coverage instead of zero.

Schema hardening:
- schemaCatalog.ts: extract shared CatalogItemTypeSchema enum (adds
  'GPU'), used by both BOMItemSchema and CatalogSKUSchema.type
  (previously an unconstrained z.string() that couldn't catch the
  switch/GPU mislabeling above). Exported CatalogItemType TS alias.
- CatalogAddForm.tsx: reuse the shared enum for the add-SKU form
  schema instead of its own looser z.string(); added GPU as a
  selectable category.
- TaxonomyGraphSidebar.tsx: fix 'Chassis Option' typo (not a valid
  category) surfaced by the tightened enum; typed the local variable
  against CatalogItemType so this class of typo fails to compile
  going forward.
- MappingPanel.test.tsx: narrow a test fixture's type field to
  satisfy the tightened enum.

Verified: tsc --noEmit clean, full vitest suite green (84 files /
387 tests, 0 regressions).
